body:
@aabanda, this sounds like an interesting and good idea.

However, what I'm wondering: is this not original research rather than just a simple improvement to an existing algorithm? In which case it might be appropriate to primarily write it up as a research paper, "correcting interval sampling bias in time series forest classifier importance curves" or sth like that?

Since if you just fix it in the code:
* the implementation might no longer be 1:1 congruent with the algorithm described in the paper (of which the class is supposed to be an "implementation mirror" i.m.o.)
* your (potentially great) idea would go unnoticed, unpublished, unreviewed

@TonyBagnall, what is your opinion?
